{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"2350","heading":"Corrosion prevention","label":"2350 Corrosion prevention","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/ch36/schV","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2350","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","References in TextThe National Apprenticeship Act, referred to in subsec. (c)(3)(B)(ii), is , , which is classified generally to chapter 4C (§ 50 et seq.) of Title 29, Labor. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under and Tables.act Aug. 16, 1937, ch. 66350 Stat. 664section 50 of Title 29","CodificationSection was enacted as part of the Water Resources Reform and Development Act of 2014, and not as part of the Water Resources Development Act of 1986 which comprises this chapter.","Amendments2025—Subsec. (c)(3), (4). added par. (3) and redesignated former par. (3) as (4).Pub. L. 118–2722016—Subsec. (d). added subsec. (d).Pub. L. 114–322","Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","“Secretary” DefinedSecretary means the Secretary of the Army, see , set out as a note under .section 2 of Pub. L. 113–121section 2201 of this title"],"amendments":["References in TextThe National Apprenticeship Act, referred to in subsec. (c)(3)(B)(ii), is , , which is classified generally to chapter 4C (§ 50 et seq.) of Title 29, Labor. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under and Tables.act Aug. 16, 1937, ch. 66350 Stat. 664section 50 of Title 29","Amendments2025—Subsec. (c)(3), (4). added par. (3) and redesignated former par. (3) as (4).Pub. L. 118–2722016—Subsec. (d). added subsec. (d).Pub. L. 114–322"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"In general","label":"a In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2350%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"To the greatest extent practicable, the Secretary shall encourage and incorporate corrosion prevention activities at water resources development projects.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Activities","label":"b Activities","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2350%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2350%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"use best practices to carry out corrosion prevention activities in the field;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2350%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/b/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2350%2Fb%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"determining protective coatings;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/b/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2350%2Fb%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"selecting materials; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/b/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2350%2Fb%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"determining methods of cathodic protection, design, and engineering for corrosion prevention;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2350%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"use certified coating application specialists and cathodic protection technicians and engineers;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/b/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2350%2Fb%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"use best practices in environmental protection to prevent environmental degradation and to ensure careful handling of all hazardous materials;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/b/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2350%2Fb%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"demonstrate a history of employing industry-certified inspectors to ensure adherence to best practices and standards; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":null,"label":"6","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/b/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2350%2Fb%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"demonstrate a history of compliance with applicable requirements of the Occupational Safety and Health Administration.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"Corrosion prevention activities defined","label":"c Corrosion prevention activities defined","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2350%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2350%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the application and inspection of protective coatings for complex work involving steel and cementitious structures, including structures that will be exposed in immersion;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2350%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the installation, testing, and inspection of cathodic protection systems;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/c/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2350%2Fc%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/c/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/c/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2350%2Fc%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"offered or accredited by an organization that sets industry standards for corrosion mitigation and prevention; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/c/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/c/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2350%2Fc%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/c/3/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/c/3/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2350%2Fc%2F3%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an employment and training activity (as defined in ); orsection 3102 of title 29","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/c/3/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/c/3/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2350%2Fc%2F3%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"registered under the Act of (commonly known as the “National Apprenticeship Act”; , chapter 663; et seq.); andAugust 16, 193750 Stat. 66429 U.S.C. 50","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/c/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2350%2Fc%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"any other activities related to corrosion prevention the Secretary determines appropriate.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":"Report","label":"d Report","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2350%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/d/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2350%2Fd%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a description of the actions the Secretary has taken to implement this section; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/d/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2350/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2350%2Fd%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a description of the projects utilizing corrosion prevention activities, including which activities were undertaken.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}
